\DOC mk_arb

\TYPE {mk_arb : hol_type -> term}

\SYNOPSIS
Creates a type instance of the {ARB} constant.

\LIBRARY

\DESCRIBE
For any HOL type {ty}, {mk_arb ty} creates a type instance of the {ARB}
constant. 

\FAILURE
Never fails.

\COMMENTS
{ARB} is a fixed but arbitrary constant of type {alpha}. It is 
occasionally useful for creating pseudo-partial functions.

\SEEALSO
dest_arb, is_arb.

\ENDDOC
